# Copy to .env and set your keys. Never commit .env.
#
# Local dev: `npm run dev` runs scripts/dev-server.cjs (static files + /api/weather like Vercel).
# Use `npm run serve:static` only if you do not need the weather proxy.
#
# ── Two API keys (often different in Google Cloud) ───────────────────────────
# GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY — Browser Maps JavaScript API key (AIza…). Used in the page for the map,
# Directions, and Places. Restrict with Application restrictions → HTTP referrers (localhost,
# 127.0.0.1, and your production domain). Enable: Maps JavaScript API, Directions API (legacy),
# Places (if you load the Places library).
#
# GOOGLE_MAPS_SERVER_KEY — Separate API key for server-side Weather requests (api/weather.js
# and scripts/dev-server.cjs). Prefer Application restrictions → None or IP, API restrictions
# → Weather API only. If unset, the proxy falls back to GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY (often fails when
# that key is referrer-locked for browser use only).
#
# If the console shows InvalidKeyMapError: GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY is wrong for this origin, missing
# Maps JavaScript API on that key, or not a Maps key at all. It is not the same value as
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID (.apps.googleusercontent.com).
#
# Required in Google Cloud (billing on; same or linked project as the keys):
#   - Maps JavaScript API
#   - Places API (or Places API New) if you use libraries=places
#   - Directions API (Legacy) — enable at:
#     https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/library/directions-backend.googleapis.com
#   - Weather API — enable at:
#     https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/library/weather.googleapis.com
#
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID — OAuth 2.0 Web client id (…apps.googleusercontent.com). Injected at build
# into google-maps-config.js as window.__GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID__ (public in the browser).
#
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET — OAuth client secret (GOCSPX-…). Server-side only; never in JS bundles
# or git. This static site does not ship it to the client; keep it for future server OAuth flows.
#
# Vercel: set GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY, GOOGLE_MAPS_SERVER_KEY (recommended), GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID, and
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET under Project → Settings → Environment Variables. Build must see the
# Maps + client id vars so scripts/inject-maps-key.js can write google-maps-config.js.

GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=
GOOGLE_MAPS_SERVER_KEY=
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=
